From 3a65f8a04be33ae58ce489313cd7b2d64bfe5e66 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw Vendor Replay <vendor-replay@rivonclaw.invalid>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 07:18:21 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): recover reply session initialization
 conflicts

Why:
- OpenClaw v2026.6.11 compares the full session entry during reply initialization, so routine metadata writes can create false CAS conflicts and silently drop rapid channel messages.
- A genuine competing session rotation can still conflict twice, so the outer unlocked initializer needs bounded retry with abort-aware backoff.

Upstream:
- 826c84ea19429ece853d62aba5b674cae90f5824 (PR #98835) narrows the revision guard to session identity and preserves concurrent metadata.
- 101b601df8acb9139dedc6070081b993dcd5fccb (PR #105754) adds typed conflict recovery with five attempts and bounded backoff.

Removal:
- Delete this patch after .openclaw-version points to a commit containing both upstream commits, or equivalent identity-only reply-session CAS plus abort-aware five-attempt outer retry behavior.

Tests:
- src/auto-reply/reply/session.init-conflict-retry.test.ts
- src/config/sessions/session-accessor.test.ts
- apps/desktop/src/gateway/vendor-session-init-conflict-retry.sentinel.test.ts
